				<td colspan="2"><span>You mean there is hope? The one thing I miss from EQ1 is running through zones at breakneck speed--just cruising. It was my favorite thing to do.  Well.. second favorite thing to do was running through zones at breakneck speed while dragging the corpses of some poor dead souls back to their owners at the zone-in.
<br />

<br />
I definitely felt that bards lost out on the runnng thing. Being only 19 atm and still sorting out the Dirge class quest, I hadnt looked ahead at &quot;songs&quot; -- or what passes for songs here in the future of Norrath.
<br />

<br />
And that's another thing-- there is no &quot;stop song&quot;. If you need to switch up a song quick like to cover a new incident you have to cancel the old song by clicking on it, hitting cancel then starting the new song-- all this while trying to answer HO's, back stab, etc etc. That is NOT bard efficiency. (Please tell me if there is another way--I'm stumbling in the dark here<img src="/skins/default/images/emotions/emotion-1.gif" border="0" alt="Smiley" hspace="2" /> )
<br />

<br />
Good to see a forum for us defectors ~~
<br />

<br />
Sonnatta from FV now known as:
